01:31:10,301 --> 01:31:12,720
I'd like to see your secret.

1041
01:31:13,680 --> 01:31:15,056
I don't know.

1042
01:31:19,980 --> 01:31:21,940
You're my boyfriend.

1043
01:31:23,109 --> 01:31:24,610
My cutie.

1044
01:31:26,948 --> 01:31:29,617
You're my dear sweet Captain...

1045
01:31:31,161 --> 01:31:33,247
and I'm Mrs Captain.

1046
01:31:34,457 --> 01:31:36,626
I don't understand that.

1047
01:31:38,796 --> 01:31:41,132
I better go home, I think.

1048
01:32:10,087 --> 01:32:15,217
Dickens has a girlfriend.
He's your boyfriend.

1049
01:32:15,469 --> 01:32:17,470
He's my husband.

1050
01:32:17,764 --> 01:32:21,518
And I... I... I...

1051
01:32:21,851 --> 01:32:23,103
I'm his wife.

1052
01:32:23,354 --> 01:32:27,068
He's dreamboat. He's a sunny cloud.

1053
01:32:27,443 --> 01:32:28,569
Kiss me.

1054
01:32:29,235 --> 01:32:32,823
- You're a girl.
- Kiss me and I'll be a boy.

1055
01:32:33,449 --> 01:32:38,664
- Girls don't kiss girls that way.
- Please.

1056
01:32:44,923 --> 01:32:46,884
Oh baby.

1057
01:32:53,016 --> 01:32:54,978
You're disgusting.

1058
01:32:55,186 --> 01:32:58,606
That was fun. That was great.

1059
01:32:58,817 --> 01:33:02,488
- You're my best friend.
- And you're mine too.

1060
01:33:02,697 --> 01:33:04,907
And I love Dickens!

1061
01:33:05,367 --> 01:33:10,163
He's the sweet prince.
He's the great king.

1062
01:33:11,039 --> 01:33:13,542
He's apply juice and jerky!

1063
01:33:13,836 --> 01:33:15,796
We're a happy family.

1064
01:33:16,006 --> 01:33:19,676
And Dell will marry daddy
and look after us all.

1065
01:33:20,176 --> 01:33:25,307
And we'll explore the Hundred
Years Ocean. It's a dream come true.

1066
01:33:25,518 --> 01:33:27,603
It's Christmas!

1067
01:33:43,123 --> 01:33:45,335
And what do we have here?

1068
01:33:47,171 --> 01:33:50,215
I think a baby is in me from kissing.

1069
01:33:50,632 --> 01:33:55,430
I think it's Mustique.
I think she's come back.

1070
01:33:56,056 --> 01:33:58,809
Tell Dickens.
Tell him about the baby.

1071
01:33:59,019 --> 01:34:03,440
Then he'll let you see his special secret.
Maybe he's alone.

1072
01:34:05,234 --> 01:34:07,363
But maybe Dell's still there.

1073
01:34:10,533 --> 01:34:11,702
Let's go.

1074
01:34:11,952 --> 01:34:15,623
Let's go see Dickens special secret
in his room.

1075
01:34:21,590 --> 01:34:24,801
My sweet honey rose

1076
01:34:25,011 --> 01:34:28,890
Strange dark flower rose

1077
01:34:29,015 --> 01:34:30,225
Jeliza-Rose

1078
01:34:47,664 --> 01:34:50,292
Hello? It's us.

1079
01:34:52,003 --> 01:34:53,965
It's Jeliza-Rose.

1080
01:34:58,052 --> 01:35:00,514
It's a real nice day for a tea party.

1081
01:35:00,974 --> 01:35:05,813
Me and Glitter Gal are here...
in case you're not too busy.

1082
01:35:43,487 --> 01:35:46,739
Jeliza-Rose. See what happens when
you're small and hungry all the time?

1083
01:35:46,990 --> 01:35:50,369
You're nasty. You deserve it.

1084
01:35:50,579 --> 01:35:53,082
Maybe I am nasty,
but at least I'm alive.

1085
01:35:53,332 --> 01:35:56,086
Get out while you can,
or she'll close a trap on you too!

1086
01:35:56,587 --> 01:36:00,841
Shut up. Shut up!

1087
01:36:02,386 --> 01:36:06,641
It's not fair! I didn't know
you were there. You scared me good!

1088
01:36:06,850 --> 01:36:09,310
No, no, it was an accident.

1089
01:36:09,645 --> 01:36:12,649
You just got spooked, that's all.

1090
01:36:12,858 --> 01:36:16,194
- It was all them ugly dead things and all.
- No, that's not right.

1091
01:36:16,488 --> 01:36:17,948
No, that's not right.

1092
01:36:18,198 --> 01:36:21,953
Because Dell makes them alive again
and that's what she does!

1093
01:36:22,162 --> 01:36:25,708
And she's Jesus how she makes
them alive again!

1094
01:36:27,001 --> 01:36:29,462
You scared me good,
I didn't know you was there!

1095
01:36:29,713 --> 01:36:31,172
I think I fainted.

1096
01:36:31,756 --> 01:36:33,091
I'm sorry.

1097
01:36:33,301 --> 01:36:36,220
Don't do that again or I'll die, okay?

1098
01:36:36,722 --> 01:36:37,849
Okay.

1099
01:36:38,975 --> 01:36:41,310
All right. I'm sorry.

1100
01:36:42,395 --> 01:36:45,524
I think I'm sorry too. Think so.

1101
01:36:50,448 --> 01:36:51,824
Dickens...

1102
01:36:53,911 --> 01:36:56,788
Glitter Gal wants to tell you something.

1103
01:37:05,634 --> 01:37:08,511
That baby sounds like a strange thing.

1104
01:37:08,721 --> 01:37:13,101
We can build a castle...
and Dell will marry my daddy.

1105
01:37:14,063 --> 01:37:15,314
But...

1106
01:37:15,814 --> 01:37:19,860
you have to show me
your special secret first.

1107
01:37:23,615 --> 01:37:26,034
No, I can't build a castle.
I don't know how.

1108
01:37:26,243 --> 01:37:29,122
I don't know how. No.

1109
01:37:31,251 --> 01:37:35,297
Dickens... if you show me your secret...

1110
01:37:36,256 --> 01:37:38,301
I'll love you forever.

1111
01:37:46,311 --> 01:37:51,109
I'll show you, okay? Just once only.

1112
01:37:52,278 --> 01:37:56,742
But if I don't unpack this bag before
Dell gets back, I won't eat tonight.

1113
01:37:56,992 --> 01:37:59,869
So you wait, okay? You wait.

1114
01:38:00,122 --> 01:38:03,041
Don't touch nothing.
This is Dell's place.

1115
01:38:03,208 --> 01:38:04,335
All right.

1116
01:38:05,293 --> 01:38:07,421
I'll wait for my cutie.

1117
01:38:08,465 --> 01:38:10,134
You're my kisser.

1118
01:38:15,390 --> 01:38:18,560
What do you wanna see his special
secret for? You're better off not knowing.

1119
01:38:18,728 --> 01:38:20,980
Look what happens. I was curious.

1120
01:38:22,233 --> 01:38:23,859
You know what Dell's gonna do to me?

1121
01:38:24,027 --> 01:38:25,362
We have to help him.

1122
01:38:26,780 --> 01:38:30,953
You do it. I don't wanna get in trouble.

1123
01:38:33,164 --> 01:38:35,625
That's it, that's it. I'm free, I'm free!

1124
01:38:55,318 --> 01:38:58,780
We can't wake mama,
so we can't talk like this...

1125
01:38:59,030 --> 01:39:01,283
unless we talk like this first.

1126
01:39:03,953 --> 01:39:05,662
Because we're ghosts.

1127
01:39:07,500 --> 01:39:11,046
- We're quiet ghosts.
- Nice.

1128
01:39:13,507 --> 01:39:16,301
Your house is the witch's cave.

1129
01:39:17,136 --> 01:39:21,059
We're disappearing
and we won't get caught.

1130
01:39:21,266 --> 01:39:23,770
Yeah, that's a good idea, I think.

1131
01:39:24,020 --> 01:39:26,774
Because Dell will wallop me
for having company.

1132
01:39:46,050 --> 01:39:48,136
It's Halloween.

1133
01:40:03,530 --> 01:40:06,742
My room! My room, my room.

1134
01:40:08,828 --> 01:40:13,626
You better get on the bed so you don't
crush nothing important, okay?

1135
01:40:13,836 --> 01:40:14,795
Okay.

1136
01:40:35,154 --> 01:40:37,114
- Is there candy in it?
- No.

1137
01:40:38,826 --> 01:40:41,162
It's my special secret.

1138
01:40:41,829 --> 01:40:45,793
It's the eight wonder.
The great wave.

1139
01:40:47,628 --> 01:40:49,546
The end of the world!

1140
01:40:49,798 --> 01:40:51,050
Dynamite.

1141
01:40:52,385 --> 01:40:55,847
- How do you explode them?
- Like a firecracker, I think.

1142
01:40:56,056 --> 01:41:00,436
Like a war bomb! Boom! Kaboom!

1143
01:41:00,686 --> 01:41:03,189
And everything gets cleaned away.

1144
01:41:03,608 --> 01:41:07,445
The end of the world. Blown to bits.

1145
01:41:08,197 --> 01:41:09,989
So I'll keep them.

1146
01:41:11,158 --> 01:41:13,912
Yeah, I'll keep them until I'm an old man...

1147
01:41:14,663 --> 01:41:19,252
and then I'll kill that shark...
and I'll be a hero...

1148
01:41:19,462 --> 01:41:20,838
I'm pretty sure.

1149
01:41:21,213 --> 01:41:25,594
And I'll help you.
That way we can be on TV.

1150
01:41:28,640 --> 01:41:30,225
Because you love me.

1151
01:41:35,189 --> 01:41:37,568
I'm your wife forever.

1152
01:41:51,043 --> 01:41:54,131
That's baby's asleep, I think.

1153
01:41:55,382 --> 01:41:57,051
It's snoring.

1154
01:41:59,095 --> 01:42:00,514
She's growing.

1155
01:42:01,682 --> 01:42:03,393
She's coming tonight...

1156
01:42:04,145 --> 01:42:05,061
or tomorrow.

1157
01:42:06,689 --> 01:42:08,649
I bet she's pretty.

1158
01:42:09,650 --> 01:42:13,155
I bet she's pretty,
I bet she's pretty like you.

1159
01:42:16,993 --> 01:42:18,621
Where's that place?

1160
01:42:20,164 --> 01:42:22,876
The whole bottom of the ocean.

1161
01:42:24,170 --> 01:42:28,716
There are whole cities there,
with people and dogs.

1162
01:42:29,010 --> 01:42:34,390
There are castles there...
and farms and husbands and wives...

1163
01:42:34,641 --> 01:42:38,814
and babies, and ghosts...

1164
01:42:39,940 --> 01:42:42,150
and silly kissers too.

1165
01:42:42,694 --> 01:42:45,113
And kissers that do this...

1166
01:43:15,944 --> 01:43:18,780
- It's mama, I think.
- Is she awake?

1167
01:43:19,240 --> 01:43:20,868
I don't know.

1168
01:43:22,078 --> 01:43:25,038
Because that never happens,
but maybe it happens.

1169
01:43:25,916 --> 01:43:29,295
If mama quit dozing
I'll go see if she wants soup.

1170
01:43:31,423 --> 01:43:32,800
Dickens, I'm scared.

1171
01:43:34,469 --> 01:43:35,887
Me too.

1172
01:43:36,180 --> 01:43:39,809
If we go together, we're safe.

1173
01:43:41,395 --> 01:43:42,729
Yeah, all right.

1174
01:44:02,713 --> 01:44:03,881
Mama?

1175
01:44:11,099 --> 01:44:12,975
It's damn bad.

1176
01:44:19,778 --> 01:44:22,905
Dell says someday mama will wake.

1177
01:44:23,157 --> 01:44:27,871
And she says someday there'll be a
pill or a story or something...

1178
01:44:28,037 --> 01:44:30,998
and that'll make her eyes
come alive again.

1179
01:44:31,208 --> 01:44:35,256
Because if she gets buried
she'll be gone for good.

1180
01:44:36,006 --> 01:44:38,050
That's my gift.

1181
01:44:41,180 --> 01:44:43,474
And that's daddy's map!

1182
01:44:44,518 --> 01:44:46,979
No, no, they're Dell's.

1183
01:44:47,980 --> 01:44:49,565
It's all hers.

1184
01:44:50,943 --> 01:44:53,194
Her place is with mama.

1185
01:45:05,043 --> 01:45:06,628
It's daddy.

1186
01:45:09,591 --> 01:45:13,179
And that's Dell.
She was beautiful once.

1187
01:45:13,387 --> 01:45:15,306
Not a pirate or a ghost.

1188
01:45:16,266 --> 01:45:19,896
She had two good eyes
and she loved your daddy.

1189
01:45:21,481 --> 01:45:23,484
They were kissers.

1190
01:45:23,775 --> 01:45:25,612
Young kissers.

1191
01:45:26,238 --> 01:45:29,365
Dell and my daddy were young kissers.

1192
01:45:29,576 --> 01:45:30,452
No.

1193
01:45:30,659 --> 01:45:32,953
They do it like we do it.

1194
01:45:33,956 --> 01:45:37,586
No, no...

1195
01:45:38,421 --> 01:45:40,381
They do it like we do it.

1196
01:45:43,135 --> 01:45:44,552
I'm Dell...

1197
01:45:44,929 --> 01:45:48,682
and you're my daddy...
and we're married...

1198
01:45:49,226 --> 01:45:51,604
and our baby's coming.

1199
01:45:58,529 --> 01:46:00,698
Filth! Evil!

1200
01:46:00,908 --> 01:46:02,576
Rotten! Rotten!

1201
01:46:02,786 --> 01:46:04,287
No, Dell!

1202
01:46:04,537 --> 01:46:09,417
Doing that in here!
Dickens, bringing that nasty...

1203
01:46:09,670 --> 01:46:12,381
- nastiness into our home!
- No, Dell, no.

1204
01:46:12,631 --> 01:46:15,050
This is my room, mama's...

1205
01:46:15,676 --> 01:46:19,681
I'm sorry, Dell, I'm sorry.

1206
01:46:19,932 --> 01:46:21,643
Like father like daughter!

1207
01:46:23,354 --> 01:46:28,527
Spy! Watching in the bushes,
you vile nasty child!

1208
01:46:28,527 --> 01:46:30,279
- I didn't do anything! - Liar!

1209
01:46:30,529 --> 01:46:31,488
Dell...

1210
01:46:31,780 --> 01:46:34,908
Spy... with your little spies!

1211
01:46:35,159 --> 01:46:36,078
No!

1212
01:46:36,537 --> 01:46:39,038
You'll starve now, you hear me?

1213
01:46:39,291 --> 01:46:41,792
No more food for you! No more you!

1214
01:46:42,043 --> 01:46:47,676
Dell, no, Dell!

1215
01:46:52,307 --> 01:46:54,976
Now. Who have we here?

1216
01:46:56,229 --> 01:46:57,646
It's Mustique!

1217
01:46:57,898 --> 01:46:59,274
A troublesome creature.

1218
01:46:59,442 --> 01:47:02,444
- She's mine! I hate you!
- I don't think so. No, no, no.

1219
01:47:05,949 --> 01:47:08,994
Now look at what you done.
Look at what you done now!

1220
01:47:10,497 --> 01:47:11,748
All right.

1221
01:47:12,000 --> 01:47:14,252
All right, my boy.

1222
01:47:14,502 --> 01:47:17,421
- Dell's here. Dell's got...
- Leave him alone!

1223
01:47:17,672 --> 01:47:19,800
- Leave him! Witch!
- Get off me!

1224
01:47:20,010 --> 01:47:21,470
Leave him!

1225
01:47:27,353 --> 01:47:28,729
Mama.

1226
01:47:31,358 --> 01:47:33,734
I've got your hat, you witch!

1227
01:47:33,944 --> 01:47:36,197
Now you'll get stung by bees and die.

1228
01:47:36,448 --> 01:47:39,326
You'll die.
And get out in the earth and die!

1229
01:47:39,577 --> 01:47:40,619
Mama.

1230
01:48:02,398 --> 01:48:03,524
You're gonna die now!

1231
01:48:13,203 --> 01:48:15,663
I didn't do anything! I didn't!

1232
01:48:16,082 --> 01:48:18,292
I didn't do anything!

1233
01:48:20,337 --> 01:48:23,381
She's got them all, daddy. I'm next.

1234
01:48:23,591 --> 01:48:27,345
When she finds the squirrel gone
she'll destroy me for sure.

1235
01:48:28,222 --> 01:48:32,270
Probably she'll hang my head
in her living room!

1236
01:48:39,988 --> 01:48:43,576
You're dreaming yourself
far away, daddy.

1237
01:48:44,911 --> 01:48:47,829
Further than the Hundred Years Ocean.

1238
01:48:50,292 --> 01:48:52,252
Beyond Jutland...

1239
01:48:53,005 --> 01:48:57,426
deep, deep, deep...
in the place where dreams are made.

1240
01:49:00,221 --> 01:49:02,140
We'll be a happy family.

1241
01:49:04,185 --> 01:49:07,774
We'll build a castle of crooked branches...

1242
01:49:08,483 --> 01:49:10,443
and flattened pennies.

1243
01:49:11,987 --> 01:49:13,322
Eat meat...

1244
01:49:13,907 --> 01:49:17,912
and butter tarts... and drink lemonade...

1245
01:49:18,162 --> 01:49:21,207
from gold-plated paper cups.

1246
01:49:24,753 --> 01:49:27,215
I'll dream myself there too.

1247
01:49:28,341 --> 01:49:32,555
If I shut my eyes and try hard enough...

1248
01:49:33,556 --> 01:49:36,726
maybe I'll wake inside your dream.

1249
01:49:59,590 --> 01:50:01,676
The end of the world.

1250
01:51:44,391 --> 01:51:45,518
Dickens!

1251
01:51:48,856 --> 01:51:53,612
You killed it!
You killed the monster shark, Dickens!

1252
01:51:55,532 --> 01:51:57,199
I love you.

1253
01:52:09,841 --> 01:52:10,926
Little girl.

1254
01:52:12,845 --> 01:52:14,264
Are you hurt?

1255
01:52:15,097 --> 01:52:16,975
Are you okay, little girl?

1256
01:52:20,939 --> 01:52:23,024
I'm hungry is all.

1257
01:52:26,154 --> 01:52:28,948
Well, here... I have something.

1258
01:52:36,835 --> 01:52:40,381
Are you traveling alone
or with someone?

1259
01:52:41,966 --> 01:52:43,176
Don't know.

1260
01:52:45,179 --> 01:52:47,597
I guess Dickens will come and get me.

1261
01:52:48,015 --> 01:52:49,935
I'm pretty sure he will.

1262
01:52:53,189 --> 01:52:55,608
So your parents weren't on the train?

1263
01:53:00,782 --> 01:53:02,867
You're all alone like me then.

1264
01:53:04,787 --> 01:53:06,497
It happened so fast.

1265
01:53:07,289 --> 01:53:08,792
So fast.

1266
01:53:09,711 --> 01:53:13,006
We're two of the lucky ones...
thank God.

1267
01:53:15,051 --> 01:53:17,970
Very, very lucky.

1268
01:53:19,097 --> 01:53:23,645
Dickens? Dickens?

1269
01:53:25,230 --> 01:53:26,858
Dickens?

1270
01:53:28,067 --> 01:53:30,569
- You stay far. - Dickens?

1271
01:53:30,945 --> 01:53:32,780
Mess elsewhere.

1272
01:53:32,990 --> 01:53:34,783
Dickens?

1273
01:53:35,076 --> 01:53:39,582
Where are you, boy? Dickens?

1274
01:53:41,501 --> 01:53:43,462
My captain.

1275
01:53:44,005 --> 01:53:46,215
It's okay. It's okay.

1276
01:53:48,676 --> 01:53:50,304
We're safe now.

1277
01:53:53,893 --> 01:53:56,354
We'll take care of each other,
how's that?

1278
01:53:57,480 --> 01:54:00,317
And I'll make sure you get
where you're going.

1279
01:54:22,345 --> 01:54:25,640
They're beautiful. Aren't they?

1280
01:54:30,855 --> 01:54:33,109
They're my friends, you know.

1281
01:54:34,362 --> 01:54:36,154
They have names.
